column5: DESCRIPTION
Aikido is a Japanese martial art focusing on self-defense that is based on harmonising your movement and intention with that of an aggressive attack.
American Football is a team sport where the objective is to score points by advancing the ball into the opposing team's end zone by running with it or throwing it to a teammate.
Flag is the fastest growing format of the game in Great Britain, encompassing schools, colleges, universities and in the community.
Angling is the sport of catching fish with a rod, line, and hook.
Archery involves using a bow and arrow to hit a stationary target. Points are then scored based on the position the arrow lands on the target.
Athletics is a collection of track and field events that involve running, jumping and throwing.
Throwing athletics track and field event.
Hammer throw is a modern day Olympic track and field event where athletes hurl a steel ball attached to a wire.
High jump is an athletic track and field event
Javelin is the athletic sport of throwing a metal spear as far as possible.
Long jump (historically called the broad jump) is a track and field event in which athletes combine speed, strength, and agility in an attempt to leap as far as possible from a take off point.
Pole vaulting is a track and field event in which the athlete uses a long, flexible pole as an aid to jump over a bar.
Shot Put is an athletic discipline that involves 'putting' a spherical weight as far as possible.
Badminton is a racket sport that involves hitting a shuttlecock over a net on indoor courts. Points are scored when the opponent is unable to return the shuttlecock before it hits the floor.
Badminton is a racket sport that involves hitting a shuttlecock over a net on indoor courts. Points are scored when the opponent is unable to return the shuttlecock before it hits the floor.
Baseball is played by two teams of nine players each. The teams take turns batting and fielding. The batting team is called the offensive team and the fielding team is called the defensive team.

Basketball is a game played by two teams of usually five players each on a rectangular court having a raised basket or goal at each end, points being scored by tossing the ball through the opponent's basket.
Deaf basketball is basketball played by individuals with hearing impairments. Sign language is used to communicate whistle blows and communication between players.

Walking Basketball provides low impact, cardio exercise, incorporating constant brisk walking. It improves fitness, and is mentally challenging. Playing as part of a team, it brings a sense of camaraderie which is fun and rewarding.
Wheelchair basketball retains most major rules and scoring of basketball, and maintains a 10-foot basketball hoop and standard basketball court.
Baton Twirling involves performing with a baton to music.
Biathlon takes place in winter combining cross-country skiing and rifle shooting.
Snooker is played using a cue and 22 snooker balls
Bobsleigh involves teams of 2 or 4 people steering a sled down a ice track as quickly as possible.
The aim of the game is to throw leather balls - coloured red or blue as close as you can to a white target ball, or jack.
Played outdoors on a flat square of grass, or indoors on an artificial surface, bowls involves throwing/rolling a ball to end up as close to a target as possible.

Boxing is fast, technical and requires very high levels of fitness. Scoring is based around technique with bouts decided by judges and the result is based on the number of punches that land in a 'target area'.
Chess boxing is a hybrid sport which involves alternating rounds of boxing and chess
Canoeing involves using a paddle to move across the water in a narrow vessel.
Canoe Polo combines paddling and ball handling skills with an exciting contact team game.

Aerobics is a form of physical exercise that combines rhythmic aerobic exercise with stretching and strength training routines with the goal of improving all elements of fitness (flexibility, muscular strength, and cardiovascular fitness).
BODYCOMBATâ„¢ is a high-energy martial arts-inspired workout that is totally non-contact.
BODYATTACKâ„¢ is the sports-inspired cardio workout for building strength and stamina.
BODY STEPâ„¢ combines basic stepping with moves like burpees, push ups and weight plate exercises to work the upper body.
A postnatal fitness programme for mums with their babies in their buggies.
Chair based exercise classes are designed to help improve strength and balance, from the comfort of a chair.
Indoor Cycling can takes place on indoors on a stationary bike.
Insanity uses MAX Interval Training to force the body to work for longer periods of time at a higher capacity than traditional workouts.
RPMâ„¢ is an indoor cycling class, set to the rhythm of motivating music.
A group exercise programme with multi-levels of jump rope skills and tricks structured into an aerobic workout.
Step involves performing aerobics on an elevated platform (the step).
Caving is the recreational pastime of exploring cave systems
Competitive cheerleading involves squads of cheerleaders competing against each other by performing routines to music that include stunts, jumps and tumbles.
Abseiling is a technique used in climbing to allow safe descent of steep terrain.
Sport Rock Climbing involves climbing a rock using fixed protection that is already inplace as they ascend.

The aim of the batting team is to score as many 'runs' as possible - running between the wickets, exchanging ends with a second batsman (the non-striker), who has been waiting near the bowler's wicket.

Kwik Cricket aims to provide children of all levels of ability and experience with an opportunity to regularly participate in a fun, introduction to cricket and to encourage fair play by all. The format is suitable for all ages but is mostly suitable for players under the age of 11.
Table Cricket is a game for everyone to play and enjoy – young or old, disabled and non-disabled – and is a great way to teach the basic rules of cricket, all on a table top.
Croquet is an ideal way to spend a summer's afternoon.
CrossFit is a strength and conditioning program consisting mainly of a mix of aerobic exercise, gymnastics (body weight exercises), and Olympic weight lifting.
Curling is a sport in which players slide stones across ice towards a circular target area.
New Age Kurling is a form of the original curling game, but adapted so that it can be played indoors on any smooth, flat surface, such as a sports hall, rather than on ice.
Cycling is a great sport, loved by millions around the world.
BMX racing is a type of off-road bicycle racing.
Handcycling involves cycling using the arms opposed to the legs.
Dance is an art form that generally refers to movement of the body, usually rhythmic and to music, used as a form of expression, social interaction or presented in a spiritual or performance setting.
Ballet is a classical dance form characterized by grace and precision of movement and by elaborate formal gestures, steps, and poses.
Ballroom dancing is a couples dance where couples move to the music using step-patterns and rhythms that match the character of a given song.
Belly dancing is originally a solo, improvised dance involving torso articulation.
Capoeira is a Brazilian martial art that combines elements of dance, acrobatics and music.
Clubbercise are choreographed dance fitness classes delivered in darkened rooms with disco lights and lasers, to 90's club anthems.
Flamenco dance is a Spanish dance form characterised by hand clapping, percussive footwork, and intricate hand, arm and body movements.
Latin dancing consists of five dances: the Rumba, Cha Cha, Samba, Paso Doble' and the Jive.
Latin American style of dance with Cuban origins.
Tap dancing is a form of dance characterised by the sounds of tap shoes striking the floor as a form of percussion.
Wheelchair dance sport is a sport which involves athletes with a physical impairment that affects the lower limbs.
Incorporates pilates and yoga with the positions, moves and techniques of Ballet.
Body Jam is a choreographed dance workout
Bokwa participants draw letters and numbers with their feet while performing an energizing and addictive cardio workout routine.
Boogie Bounce is a 'fat burning' class on mini trampolines with stability handles.
Booiaka is a freestyle dance class meaning 'it's the way you move'
Fitness League is used to deliver 'Bagot Stack' which is designed to improve posture and well-being through core stability and rhythmic exercise to music.
FitSteps was designed by Natalie Lowe and Ian Waite of â€˜Strictly Come Dancingâ€™ and delivers a mixture of Ballroom and Latin.
Jazzercise classes combine dance-based cardio with strength training to music.
Pole dancing is a form of performance art and fitness, which combines dance and acrobatics centered on a vertical pole.
Zumba Gold® is designed for active older adults who are looking for a modified Zumba® class that recreates the original moves but at a lower-intensity.
Zumba® for kids
Diving is a sport where the diver jumps into a pool from a platform or springboard at a range of heights.
Dodgeball is a game in which players try to hit other players on the opposing team with balls while avoiding being hit themselves.
Horse riding, or equestrian sport, refers to the skill of training and riding horses.
Dressage is a competitive equestrian sport
Eventing combines the three elements of Dressage, Show Jumping and Cross Country.
Riding on a pony through the countryside
Show jumping takes place over a course of obstacles, which can include verticals, spreads, double and triple combinations, usually with many turns and changes of direction.
There are three types of fencing - epee, foils and sabre.
Wheelchair fencing is Fencing for the physically disabled.
Floorball is a type of floor hockey with five field players and a goalkeeper on each team.
Football is widely considered to be the most popular sport in the world. The beautiful game is England's national sport
While the core game remains the same as sighted football, there are a few alterations to make football accessible to people with visual impairments.
Futsal is the global format for indoor small-sided football and the worlds fastest growing indoor sport.
Walking football is a variant of football that is aimed at keeping people aged over-50 involved with football.
Powerchair is a competitive team sport for people with disabilities who use power wheelchairs.
Footgolf is played on a golf course using a size 5 football.
Gaelic Football is a combination of rugby and football.
Geocaching is the real-world treasure hunt that's happening right now, all around you. There are 2,775,063 active geocaches and over 15 million geocachers worldwide.
Gliding involves flying in an engine-less aircraft
The object of the game is to score a goal by bowling the ball along the floor so that it crosses the goal line of the opposing team.
Golf is an adaptable game that it suits everyone, whatever their age, fitness level or ability. Whether you want to keep healthy, burn calories or spend time with friends, golf is for you.
Golf Xtreme is the golf game and programme for secondary schools
Speedgolf is a fun, fast, and fitness-oriented alternative to traditional golf.
Variation of golf that involves playing as a team.
A 'mini' version of golf designed specifically for young children at infant, primary and junior schools.
Gymnastics is an acrobatic sport which requires strength, agility and co-ordination.
Artistic gymnastics is a discipline of gymnastics where gymnasts perform short routines on different apparatus
Rhythmic Gymnastics discipline within Gymnastics
Handball is a team sport that requires you to score by throwing a ball into a goal.
Team, ball game played with sticks.
Ashtanga is an advanced form of yoga that focuses on building strength and flexibility through flow sequenced postures.
BODY BALANCEâ„¢ is a combination workout of Yoga, Tai Chi and Pilates.
Hatha Yoga stretches are referred to as 'postures' that are performed slowly and gently rather than energetically and is suitable for all levels.
Pilates improves flexibility, builds strength and develops control and endurance in the body.
Qigong practices can be classified as martial, medical, or spiritual.
Tai chi combines deep breathing and relaxation with slow and gentle movements.
Yoga is an ancient form of exercise that focuses on strength, flexibility and breathing to boost physical and mental wellbeing.
A six-a-side game on ice that involves trying to get the puck in your opponents net using your stick.
Ice skating involves dancing or racing on ice.
Figure skating involves performing on ice as an individual, duo or in a group.
Speed skating involves skating round a circuit as fast as possible to win the race.
A defensive martial art.
Judo is an dynamic combat sport represented in the Olympics.
Karate is a striking martial art
In all forms of kayaking you use a double bladed paddle and will be in a seated position with your legs in front of you.
Kickboxing is a martial art that predominately involves kicking.
Kobudo is a multi-weapon martial art.
Korfball is a fast-paced and dynamic game that is the only truly mixed team ball sport in the world.
Kung Fu is a Chinese Martial Art used for self-defense.
Lacrosse is a team game where goals are scored by shooting a ball into a net, using a stick with a pocket on the end, called a crosse.
Lifesaving Sport is a competitive sport that gives you the opportunity to compete with fellow lifesavers and grow your essential lifesaving skills.
Mixed Martial Arts is a full-contact combat sport
Modern Pentathlon is a multi-discipline sport
Motorsport is a group of motorised racing sports.
Speedway bikes have no brakes, just one gear, a clutch and 500cc engines which run on methanol fuel
Mountain biking involves cycling off road.
A combination of hill walking and scrambling to climb a mountain
Muay Thai is a form of martial arts and orginates from Thailand.
Netball is a team game which involves shooting a ball through a hoop
Ninjitsu is the ancient art of the ninja shadow warriors of Japan.
Octopush is underwater hockey
Orienteering is a challenging outdoor adventure sport

Parkour / Freerunning / Art du Deplacement is the non-competitive physical discipline of training to move freely over and through any terrain using only the abilities of the body, principally through running, jumping, climbing and quadrupedal movement.
Pétanque is a form of boules normally played on hard dirt or gravel

A paddle sport created for all ages and skill levels. The rules are simple and the game is easy for beginners to learn, but can develop into a quick, fast-paced, competitive game for experienced players.
Equestrian team sport.
Polybat endeavours to provide youngsters with more severe impairments, who cannot play recreational table tennis, with a suitable bat/ball net type game (with the net removed).
Racketball is played on any regular squash court and is similar to squash.
White water rafting is a sport which uses an inflatable raft to navigate a rough river with a team steered by a tour guide at the stern.
Roller Derby is an all-girl contact sports.
Roller hockey is a form of hockey played on a dry surface using roller skates, skates with wheels.
Travelling using skates with wheels.
Roller skiing is an off-snow equivalent to cross-country skiing that takes place on smooth surfaces such as paths in parks, safe roads and cycle tracks.
The sport of Rounders is a fun, exciting, striking and fielding team game, where points known as 'Rounders' are scored by a player hitting a ball and then completing a circuit of the track.
Rowing can be either recreational or competitive, indoor or outdoor.
Rugby league is a full contact game, played by two teams of 13 players.
Rugby union is a contact sport where aim is to use the ball to score more points than the other team.
Touch rugby differs from rugby through the method of tackling which involves touching the opponents using their hands on any part of the body, clothing, or the ball.
Running is a form of exercise that can be done at anytime and anywhere.
Sailing and windsurfing are two great sports for getting you active and energetic, outside in the fresh air.
Sailing is one of the very few sports in which able-bodied sailors and disabled sailors can participate on equal terms.
Scuba diving is a form of underwater diving in which a diver uses a self-contained underwater breathing apparatus (scuba) to breathe underwater.
Target shooting today is a popular sport, comprising over 41 different disciplines across 3 main categories (Fullbore Rifle & Pistol, Small-bore Rifle & Pistol, and Shotgun)
Clay pigeon shooting is the art of shooting at special flying targets with a shotgun.
Skateboarding is an action sport which involves riding and performing tricks using a skateboard.

Skiing is a popular sport that takes place on snow, artificial surfaces and more recently, on indoor artificial snow slopes. It can be undertaken as a leisure activity or competitive sport and is suitable for most ages.
Snowboarding combines elements of skiing, skateboarding and surfing.
Softball is a direct descendant of Baseball, only the ball is bigger and the game is more fun.
The game is played by two players (or four players for doubles) with standard rackets in a four-walled court with a small hollow rubber ball.
Stoolball is a team sport, similar to Twenty20 cricket.
Aerial discipline is a collections of aerial activities which include the use of vertical rope, silks tissu, straps, static trapeze and hoop.
BODYPUMPâ„¢ is using light to moderate weights with lots of repetition to provide a total body workout.

Boxercise is an effective form of cross training that incorporates a combination of boxing movements and aerobics. This makes a fun alternative and also improves rhythm, co-ordination as well as burning calories!
The Boxfit classes are an all-level circuit training class.
Kettlebell classes use a cast iron weight with a handle to perform exercises to core muscle groups to develops dynamic strength.
This class focuses on toning up legs, bums and tums.
A class using a Swiss ball to work on core strengthening, including the abdominal muscles which help to improve your balance.
Surfing is a surface water sport in which a person rides on a moving wave on a surf board.
Unlike traditional surfing where the rider is sitting until a wave comes, stand up paddle boarders maintain an upright stance on their boards and use a paddle to propel themselves through the water.
Swimming is an excellent form of exercise as it gives a full-body workout.
Synchronised swimming (synchro) is an exciting mixture of swimming, dance and gymnastics performed mostly by women.
Table tennis is an Olympic sport where two for four players hit a ball with paddles back and forth to each other on a table which is divided with a net.
Taekwondo is a Korean martial art.
Tchoukball is a fast and exciting sport that is typically played indoors however beach, grass and wheel chair versions are great alternatives
The player rolls a ball to knock over as many pins as possible.
Tennis involves hitting a ball over a net using a racket.
Deaf tennis has a long history in British tennis and playing the sport requires no adaption apart from making sure communication is clear between players, coaches and officials.
The sport is derived from tennis, and the name comes from the English word paddle, referring to the paddles players use during play.
Trampolining is a competitive Olympic sport in which gymnasts perform acrobatics while bouncing on a trampoline.
Triathlon is an exciting multi-discipline sport made up of a swim, then a bike ride and then a run.
The sport of aquathlon consists of a continuous, two-stage race involving swimming followed by running.
The object is to pull the opposing team a distance of four metres.
Ultimate is an exciting, non-contact team sport.
Volleyball is an Olympic team sport in which two teams of 6 players are separated by a net.
Beach Volleyball is a variation of Volleyball that takes place on sand instead of a hard court.
Sitting volleyball has grown to be one of the more popular Paralympic sports due to the fast and exciting action.
Wakeboarding is a surface water sport which involves riding a wakeboard over the surface of a body of water.
Walking is the easiest, most accessible, cost effective, and enjoyable way for most people to increase their physical activity.
Wallball is a sport in which players compete by hitting a ball against a wall with their hands. It is played all over the world and after being accepted as an official World Games sport.
Water polo is a fast-paced sport played by two teams in a swimming pool.
Aquafit is shallow and deep water aerobics.
Aquafit is shallow and deep water aerobics.
Zumba crossed with traditional aqua fitness disciplines creating a challenging, body-toning water-based workout.
Olympic Weight Lifting is one of the world's oldest competitive sports.
As one of the only full-contact disability sports, it is little wonder wheelchair rugby, aka 'murderball' was one of the biggest hits of the London 2012 Paralympic Games.
Windsurfing is a surface water sport that combines elements of surfing and sailing.

Wrestling is a sport as old as mankind itself. Since the dawn of time men have been pitted against each other in physical hand-to-hand combat, making this almost certainly the most ancient of Olympic sports.
